The parameter weekday is true if it is a weekday, and the parameter vacation is true if we are on vacation. 
We sleep in if it is not a weekday or we're on vacation. Return true if we sleep in.

sleepIn(false, false) → true
sleepIn(true, false) → false
sleepIn(false, true) → true

public boolean sleepIn(boolean weekday, boolean vacation) {  
  /*
    return true when it is not a weekday or on vacation
  */
  
  return (!weekday || vacation);
}

/*
Translation of Description:
  sleepIn takes two booleans, weekday and vacation, and returns true if it is 
  not a weekday or we're on vacation  

Intermediate translations:
  not a weekday -> !weekday
  on vacation -> vacation
  or -> ||
  
solution: 
   return true when (not weekday or on vacation)
*/
